headline: Robinhood faces review in EU over tokenized OpenAI, SpaceX shares - CNBC
summary: Investing.com -- The Bank of Lithuania has launched a probe into Robinhood’s (NASDAQ:HOOD) new blockchain-based “Stock Tokens,” following concerns raised by OpenAI over their association with the tokens. The central bank confirmed to CNBC on Monday that it had reached out to Robinhood for further details on the structure and marketing of tokens linked to private companies like OpenAI and SpaceX.
